# Summary
This documentation explains performance and scaling in Amplitude Experiments, highlighting the three key components needed for effective experimentation: robust ID validation, user metadata access, and behavioral cohort access. It provides implementation recommendations including using local defaults and client-side caching, and describes the architecture built on Fastly CDN and AWS services.

